                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.76/100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 18, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>532. Colombian Foreign Office informs me that Radiodifusora National has
                    suspended broadcasting on 6260 kilocycles to avoid the <pb facs="0866" n="852"
                        xml:id="pg_852"/> interference mentioned in Department’s telegram 326 of
                    March 11, 7 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
